### ============================================================================
### ANIME ROUTES (AniList Integration)
### ============================================================================

@baseUrl = http://localhost:5000/api/anime

### Get Trending Anime
GET {{baseUrl}}/trending?page=1&perPage=10

### Get Seasonal Anime (Winter 2024)
GET {{baseUrl}}/seasonal?season=WINTER&year=2024&page=1

### Search for Anime
GET {{baseUrl}}/search?q=Frieren

### Get Detailed Info by ID
GET {{baseUrl}}/info/154587

### Get Episode List for an ID
GET {{baseUrl}}/episodes/154587

### Search Torrents for a Specific Episode
# Finds magnets from Nyaa/Prowlarr without starting a download
GET {{baseUrl}}/episode-torrents?title=Frieren&episode=1&quality=1080p&sources=nyaa,prowlarr

### Search Batch/Complete Series Torrents
GET {{baseUrl}}/batch-torrents?title=Cyberpunk+Edgerunners

---

### ============================================================================
### TORRENT ROUTES (Search & WebTorrent Management)
### ============================================================================

@torrentUrl = http://localhost:5000/api/torrent

### Search Nyaa directly
GET {{torrentUrl}}/nyaa?q=Sousou+no+Frieren+01

### Parallel Search (Nyaa + Prowlarr)
GET {{torrentUrl}}/search?q=One+Piece+1000

### Start a Download
# Replace the magnet link with a real one for testing
POST {{torrentUrl}}/download
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "magnet": "magnet:?xt=urn:btih:EXAMPLE_HASH_HERE&dn=Anime_Episode"
}

### List All Active Downloads
GET {{torrentUrl}}/downloads

### Get Stats for a Specific Download
# Replace :infoHash with a real hash from the /downloads list
@activeHash = EXAMPLE_HASH_HERE
GET {{torrentUrl}}/downloads/{{activeHash}}

### Delete a Download (and files)
DELETE {{torrentUrl}}/downloads/{{activeHash}}?deleteFiles=true

---

### ============================================================================
### PLAYER ROUTES (MPV Automation)
### ============================================================================

@playerUrl = http://localhost:5000/api/player

### Check MPV Installation Status
GET {{playerUrl}}/check

### Play a Direct Stream URL (HLS/Direct MP4)
POST {{playerUrl}}/play/stream
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "url": "http://commondatastorage.googleapis.com/gtv-videos-bucket/sample/BigBuckBunny.mp4",
  "title": "Big Buck Bunny Test",
  "volume": 80,
  "fullscreen": false
}

### FULL PIPELINE: Search -> Add Torrent -> Buffer -> Launch MPV
# This triggers the automated workflow in your /play/episode route
POST {{playerUrl}}/play/episode
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "animeTitle": "Boku no Kokoro no Yabai Yatsu",
  "episodeNumber": 1,
  "quality": "1080p",
  "sources": "nyaa"
}

### List Active MPV Sessions
GET {{playerUrl}}/sessions

### Get Status of a Session
# Replace :sessionId with the ID returned from the play commands
@sessionId = SESSION_ID_HERE
GET {{playerUrl}}/sessions/{{sessionId}}

### Stop/Kill a Specific Session
DELETE {{playerUrl}}/sessions/{{sessionId}}

### Kill ALL Active MPV Processes
DELETE {{playerUrl}}/sessions

### Play a Local File (Careful with paths)
POST {{playerUrl}}/play/local
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "filePath": "C:/Downloads/Anime/Episode01.mkv",
  "title": "Local Playback Test"
}